 continue to go down since its cable is still tight.";i:2;s:65:"I released the safety handle but the chain drive is still jammed.";i:3;s:68:"The cable side is extremely tight the chain side is extremely loose.";i:4;s:73:"The door-rail connector is at the end closest to the door since the door.";i:5;s:25:"Lodged Garage Door Track.";i:6;s:92:"Your jammed garage door can be caused by something as simple as an obstruction in the track.";i:7;s:111:"Check to see if anything a shovel broom etc fell and is now stuck in the track that is causing it to be lodged.";i:8;s:71:"This can be a quick fix by identifying the object and then removing it.";i:9;s:37:"Fixing your broken garage door chain.";i:10;s:138:"When your garage door breaks down on you because of your openers chain then there really isnt much you can do aside from trying to fix it.";i:11;s:141:"Dealing with your busted garage door opener chain can sound really difficult and intimidating however in reality it can be really easy to do.";i:12;s:108:"Poor lubrication is a very common and easy to fix explanation for why you might find your garage door stuck.";i:13;s:148:"You should properly lubricate your garage doors track the opener chain and the springs every few months as part of regular preventative maintenance.";i:14;s:73:"Be sure to use Clopays Garage Door ProLube or sillicone based lubricants.";i:15;s:11:"Do not use.";i:16;s:72:"The part that connects the chain drive to the door is called a carriage.";i:17;s:184:"If this is what you are describing it sounds like your travel limit switch for ending the opening travel has either come loose and slipped out of alignment with the carriage or broken.";i:18;s:157:"The issue with the stuck trolley was because the motor was rotating in the opposite direction and causing the trolley to hit the bolt on the garage door end.";i:19;s:130:"I had to remove the chain and let the trolley rotate through once cycle and then put the chain back on to get the trolley in sync.";i:20;s:46:"How to fix a chain on a jammed roller shutter.";i:21;s:156:"At Safe Secure we offer a wide range of roller garage doors and roller shutters made from only the highest quality materials to ensure safety and longevity.";i:22;s:82:"Whether for domestic or commercial use well have the solution thats right for you.";i:23;s:45:"For any issues you do have we have a team of.";i:24;s:108:"Your garage doors track and the openers chain both require sufficient lubrication in order to do their jobs.";i:25;s:79:"If either one is under-lubed the door can become stuck when opening or closing.";i:26;s:72:"To fix this problem you will need to add more lubrication to both parts.";i:27;s:141:"Theres a reason why the door got stuck and often times that reason can be traced back to a lack of proper maintenance or service on the door.";i:28;s:78:"Here are a half dozen of the most common reasons a garage door will get stuck.";i:29;s:119:"Poor Lubrication - If your doors motor has a chain drive the chain needs to be lubricated on a regular basis just like.";i:30;s:27:"Door Lock May Be Activated.";i:31;s:22:"Disable the door lock.";i:32;s:26:"Hums For About 30 Seconds.";i:33;s:56:"The Door May Not Be Connected to the Garage Door Opener.";i:34;s:64:"You may see the rack along the inside of the rail of the opener.";i:35;s:55:"Ensure the door is connected to the garage door opener.";i:36;s:62:"What could be causing my garage door opener chain to not move.";i:37;s:28:"This question is from Quora.";i:38;s:46:"As of today 2017-11-08 there were two answers.";i:39;s:91:"Both were something along the lines of either there is no power or the gears are destroyed.";i:40;s:37:"Actually there are many more answers.";i:41;s:49:"1 Check to make sure the opener is getting power.";i:42;s:159:"- Manually pushed door up so that it locks onto the chain again ready to be operated and then pulled and pushed the door a bit to try to get the chain to move.";i:43;s:177:"It did move a tiny bit and when I try to operate the door by pressing the main button on the remote a couple of times there was a slight burr sound from the motor and the chain.";i:44;s:95:"Jammed Garage Door Opener I have a Craftsman garage door opener that has jammed at up position.";i:45;s:133:"When I activate opener to lower door it hums stays up and tension remains on chain as though opener is trying to continue pulling up.";i:46;s:121:"If your warehouse door is stuck in the open position your business security and functionality is immediately compromised.";i:47;s:152:"A functioning warehouse door is essential for every businesss safety protection and operation so getting your warehouse door to close again is critical.";i:48;s:111:"Just as with most issues with commercial doors finding the cause of the problem is the first step to fixing it.";i:49;s:81:"However the chain has completely stopped moving and by extension so has the door.";i:50;s:100:"This causes the motor to run for an extensive period of time before it seems to timeout and give up.";i:51;s:58:"The chain and door connector assembly havent budged since.";i:52;s:92:"Ive not worked on garage doors before but I have a degree in ComputerElectrical Engineering.";i:53;s:61:"Your garage door seems to get stuck while opening or closing.";i:54;s:62:"This can often be due to a problem with the tracks or rollers.";i:55;s:120:"Check the tracks to confirm they are clean and free of debris that can get in the way of the rollers and make them stop.";i:56;s:58:"Garage Door Chain Stuck 10 out of 10 based on 103 ratings.";i:57;s:90:"Mesa Garage Doors is the 1 residential garage doors company in all of Southern California.";i:58;s:116:"Garage doors that are operated by chains and run on a chain drive opener tend to deal with problems of loose chains.";i:59;s:136:"This can be hazardous for you and your loved ones mainly if this isnt addressed immediately because your garage door can jump off track.";i:60;s:60:"Garage door chains can get worn out due to the constant use.";i:61;s:72:"2 Close your garage door and disconnect the motor from the power outlet.";i:62;s:64:"3 Check the chains first and inspect for rust and other damages.";i:63;s:54:"Also see if the chains detached from the opener motor.";i:64;s:66:"4 Check the carriage assembly next and examine for misplaced nuts.";i:65;s:119:"Your garage door is an important feature on your home so you need to be able to rely on it without having any problems.";i:66;s:170:"If you find that your garage door is past its prime trust Feldco to provide you with a steel garage door thatll stand the test of time and work flawlessly through it all.";}}